PropHouse is seen as an entry point for builders to prove and test their proposal concepts, and authenticity and enable future on-chain proposals (in theory).
But it is an excellent execution for small activations.

Palace Nouns

What are we learning from this?

Your track record of good execution doesn't matter if you're not a Noun. (In some cases, because your proposal is so surreal, the hypothesis is raised that it is an extremely structured scam, even if you have already created several materials without requesting financing, and previously approved projects)

All previous ideas in this same thread were accepted with minimal introduction and were extremely flawed, but quickly taken into consideration as they came from other Nouns. Example; MadHappy and other ideas that didn't make an impact. (Content present in the proposal without details is a red flag)

None of the builders' previous ideas had a history of building for the DAO, this is a red flag that is ignored (and not questioned) if you create extremely perfect text, but only visual. - Financing a collection and show during NYFW (not delivered).
Palace Nouns is a project in which, from the beginning, the participation of nounders was something we considered and contacted, but without a response.

(nounders are already extremely overloaded with several other problems, so we took over and moved forward with the project) But don't ask for authenticity if you weren't interested, this is high-end corporate market sir, not an idea for building a sticker for a coffee shop.
Comparing Dopamine and MadHappy to Palace is like comparing a thrift store in central London to Prada. (different customers, different numbers, excessively greater impact)

Different corporations = individual approaches (it's very naive to assume that the nuances of a given market are the same as previous and smaller collaborations, brands like Palace don't sell building a collaboration just to a small community).

It is extremely illusory to build proliferation without understanding the nuances of the market. Building your own world is 100% more tangible than directing proliferation and wanting bold proposals to be raised without having a ‚Äúnorth star‚Äù.
This is avoided if nounders contact is direct with the brand and establishes communication parameters, this cuts out noise.

In a collaboration like this, you not only consider the product created, but the impact it creates in different markets. If Nounders are interested, we are happy to put them in touch, we are passionate about the Nouns vibe, but this is one of the proposals that we cannot execute alone.

We appreciate all the feedback received, even the exaggeratedly harmful ones, but it's still something we want to build on, we have several other ideas too and our story for Nouns is just beginning - we are small builders but with big connections.
